// A pure (unannotated) function lifts every domain slot onto one shared
// __Dom, so it cannot directly RETURN a mixed-domain aggregate: enumerate's
// index is @const but the lifted return type wants it clocked, and
// aggregate elements are invariant (planning/tuples.md). Write explicit
// domains, or consume enumerate in a `for`/`let`. When dependency-aware
// lifting lands this will typecheck — the ratchet will say so.
fn f (v: Vec(3, uint(8))) -> Vec(3, (integer, uint(8))) {
    v.enumerate()
}
